  <div class='user_head'>
    <h3><a href="441" class="fn n" id="id_441" name="id_441">Mark Gross</a></h3>
        <span class='affiliation org'>Intel</span>
      </div>
  <div class='user_body'>
    <div class='user_links'>
      <ul>
                
          <li>Website: <a href="http://thegnar.org/" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;" rel="nofollow">http://thegnar.org/</a></li>
        
        
          <li>Blog: <a href="http://thegnar.org/sync" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;" rel="nofollow">http://thegnar.org/sync</a></li>
        
        
          <li>Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/markgross" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;" rel="nofollow">markgross</a></li>
        
        
        
              </ul>
    </div>

  
    <h4>Biography</h4>
    <div class='note'>
      <p>(draft &#8211; will update later)<br />
Mark Gross works in the Intel Ultra Mobile Group at Intel and is focused on enabling Android on Intel based handset and tablet platforms. (Moorestown at the moment)</p>
<p>Mark is also active in power linux kernel power management, mostly through PM-QoS, and has been participating in the Linux kernel for around 10 years.</p>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
    

  
